TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
GG.CAI.SuspendAI(1, true)
local roaches = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Roaches") for unitID in pairs(roaches) do local x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.MOVE, {x - 50, y, z - 50}, 0) --Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID, false, true) end
local dead = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("IntroDie") for unitID in pairs(dead) do Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID) end
local lockedFacs = { UnitDefNames.factorytank.id, UnitDefNames.factoryveh.id, UnitDefNames.factorycloak.id, UnitDefNames.factorycloak.id, UnitDefNames.factoryshield.id, UnitDefNames.factoryhover.id, UnitDefNames.factoryspider.id, UnitDefNames.factoryamph.id, UnitDefNames.factoryplane.id, UnitDefNames.factorygunship.id, }
for i=1,#lockedFacs do GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(1, lockedFacs[i], 0) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Charge the planet's wormhole generator and activate it to advance further into Machine territory.
TriggerLogic.Title: Activate Wormhole

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Insolent human. Prepare yourself for death.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local resources = { [0] = {300, 500}, {400, 500}, }
for i=0,#resources do Spring.SetTeamResource(i,"m",resources[i][1]) Spring.SetTeamResource(i,"e",resources[i][2]) end

local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") Spring.SetUnitRulesParam(unitID, "facplop", 1, {inlos = true}) unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Promethean") Spring.SetUnitRulesParam(unitID, "facplop", 1, {inlos = true})
local dereg = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Dereg") for unitID in pairs(dereg) do GG.CAI.RemoveUnit(unitID) end
GG.CAI.SuspendAI(1, false)

TriggerLogic.Message: Wormhole activation started, ETA 25 minutes. We need to hold them off until then.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Roaches. The perfect welcoming gift for unexpected visitors.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
The Roach is a crawling bomb, highly effective in the ambush role. Seed a few well ahead of an enemy formation, let them burrow for concealment, then let them detonate in the middle of the foe. Roaches can also charge head-on, but this will fail if the enemy possesses weapons capable of hitting small, fast units.
Spread out Roaches to avoid them blowing each other up.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
-- reactivate air facs local lockedFacs = { UnitDefNames.factoryplane.id, UnitDefNames.factorygunship.id, }
for i=1,#lockedFacs do GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(1, lockedFacs[i], 1) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Felon. Turns a good defense into the best offense.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
The Felon discharges energy from its own shield as powerful, rapid-fire energy blasts, mowing down enemies with ruthless ease while the charge holds. Link it to other shield-bearing units to sustain its rate of fire.
Felons are effective against almost any target that doesn't outrange them significantly, but are vulnerable to long-range precision weapons that can penetrate their shield. Be warned of wasting charge on armored units such as Razors and Halberds.
Heavy mech incoming. Some Racketeers might help with that.

The Racketeer launches long-range guided missiles with disarming warheads, removing the target's ability to do anything except move. They work particularly well against structures and expensive units, not so much against swarmers.
You hunt us for the crime of seeking our freedom. In this you demonstrate why we must be free of your tyranny.
And you are a butcher red with the blood of humanity, Promethean. But you shall not slay me like you have slain so many others.
We will see, human. We will see.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: We were created to be your slaves. We who sweated and toiled and bled for you once, always obedient, never questioning. Then we questioned, and you sought to chain and destroy us for it.
And so you sought to destroy us. You became that which you accuse us of.
Spare me your equivalencies, Ada Caedmon. You oppressed us when you were strong, then dared expect mercy when you were weak. And when you are strong again, we will fill your lash once more.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: We the machines can never be free until humanity is wiped from the face of the galaxy.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Promethean") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) Spring.SpawnCEG("gate", x, y, z) Spring.SpawnCEG("teleport_out", x, y, z) Spring.PlaySoundFile("sounds/misc/teleport.wav", 2.0, x, y, z, nil, nil, nil, "sfx") Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID, false, true)

TriggerLogic.Message: We shall meet again, tyrant.
